summary:
Never understood why people love Charizard 🙄
The anime made me care more about the starters before I even played Pokémon yellow...
body:
Never understood why people love Charizard 🙄

The anime made me care more about the starters before I even played Pokémon yellow so that’s why I love Bulbasaur and have been a grass starter person in every game since.

Bulbasaur was awesome and took care of other Pokémon in the forest before he met Ash and after at Oak’s lab

Squirtle was a gang member who left a life of crime behind then became a fire fighter and reformed his fellow gang members to do good instead.

Charmander was rescued from certain death by Ash and what did he do? Evolve into an ungrateful teenager and then to a wannabe dragon who was an asshole to everyone specially Ash for like 2 whole regions and 3 movies, oh and left him for some girl from the valley.

Anyways this has been my unsolicited Charizard rant for today 😁

summary: Pokemon Fanfiction Chapter 4 part 3: Our First Battle. A Sticky Situation
title: Pokemon Fanfiction Chapter 4 part 3: Our First Battle. A Sticky Situation
body:
He touched the wall and felt electricity surge through his body as he touched it. As he felt around it quickly he noticed it was in the shape of a triangle. As he was looking around the wall he noticed small gray spherical ball creatures on each end of the triangular wall. He knew they were Pokémon because they had one eye that blinked occasionally. They were Magnemite[1]! He looked straight up to see it. A Magnezone[2]. Only one person could create these electromagnetic force fields, and control Magnemites with her Magnezone.

“Oh shit,” Alex said aloud as he was looking up.

Before Wendell could look up five Magnemite appeared around him, created an electromagnetic pyramid around him and carried him up in the sky towards the large gray Pokémon. Alex looked around to see more Magnemite come down and create a pyramid force field and do the same to him. He pounded on the wall. But what about Igneel!?

Meanwhile as Weedle tried to insert himself more into Charmander, two small spherical magnets appeared in between and repelled Weedle off. Before the larva could fight them off or escape they electrocuted him and before it flew onto the grass, the small Magnemite created a force field like stretcher and carried him up to the sky. The giant web crumbled as the Weedle was defeated and carried away, and Igneel was finally free. The small golden lizard coughed and collapsed onto the grass, unconscious and barely breathing.

As Wendell and Alex were being lifted he was trying to think of the best excuse to avoid her gaze and whatever punishment that was about to unfold. Please please don’t tell me I’m never going to be a trainer after just one battle; Arceus just give me one more chance, he thought and prayed to himself. As they flew up closer to the Magnezone they saw her sitting atop, very angry. The Dean of PokeAcademy.

[1] Magnemite, the magnet Pokémon. Magnemite is an electric/ steel type Pokémon. The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

[2] Magnezone, the magnet area Pokémon. Magenzone is an electric/steel type Pokémon and the final evolution of Magnemite. There are still people who believe that this Pokémon came from outer space. It emanates a powerful magnetic field.
